    <s1 name="Contributing to HOWL">
      <p>
        As an open source project, the HOWL team welcomes contributions.
      </p>
      <s2 name="What to contribute?">
        <p>
          You can contribute to HOWL by participating in discussions
          on the <a href="http://forge.objectweb.org/mail/?group_id=92">mail lists</a>,
          by submitting 
          <a href="http://forge.objectweb.org/tracker/?atid=100092&amp;group_id=92&amp;func=browse">
            bug reports
          </a>
          and
          <a href="http://forge.objectweb.org/tracker/?atid=350092&amp;group_id=92&amp;func=browse">
            feature requests
          </a>.
          <br/>
          Developers who discover and report bugs in HOWL code are
          encouraged to provide suggested corrections in the form of
          <a href="http://forge.objectweb.org/tracker/?atid=300092&amp;group_id=92&amp;func=browse">
            patches.
          </a>
          <br/>
        </p>
        <p>
          All contributions are important and help improve the quality of C-JDBC.
        </p>
      </s2>
    </s1>
  </body>
